The Luyha community will no longer be slaves or remain politically irrelevant after the naming of Musalia Mudavadi as its spokesperson, ANC Coast secretary general Jimmy Azangu has said.He said the Mulembe community at the Coast will support Mudavadi&rsquo;s presidential bid and his quest to unite Kenyans under the National Super Alliance. Azangu said Luhyas at the Coast have started campaigns. &ldquo;Ours is to ensure Mudavadi takes over as the President. Only unity will help us realise our goal,&rdquo; he said.Azangu spoke at Little Theatre Club in Mombasa town on Tuesday. ANC Coast organising secretary Tyson Mukoya urged other leaders to support Mudavadi.&ldquo;We have our Biblical Joshua and fully believe he will take us to the promised land,&rdquo; he said. Luhya elder Martin Soita endorsed the decisions made and declarations passed in Bukhungu Stadium on Saturday under the stewardship of Cotu secretary general Francis Atwoli.